  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What companies and startups use GitHub?",
  "response": "GitHub is a widely used platform for code hosting, collaboration, and version control, and many companies and startups leverage its features for their development workflows. While it's not possible to provide an exhaustive list, here are some notable examples:\n\n### Large Companies:\n1. **Microsoft**: Microsoft owns GitHub and uses it extensively for various projects, including the development of their software and open-source initiatives.\n2. **Google**: Google utilizes GitHub for some of their open-source projects and collaboration.\n3. **Facebook**: Facebook hosts many of its open-source projects on GitHub.\n4. **Amazon**: Amazon Web Services (AWS) uses GitHub for various tools and services.\n5. **IBM**: IBM leverages GitHub for its open-source projects and collaborations.\n6. **Netflix**: Netflix uses GitHub for hosting open-source projects related to their platform.\n7. **Airbnb**: Airbnb uses GitHub for various open-source initiatives.\n8. **Uber**: Uber hosts several open-source projects on GitHub.\n9. **Spotify**: Spotify uses GitHub for collaboration on open-source projects.\n10. **Twitter**: Twitter has several open-source projects hosted on GitHub.\n\n### Notable Startups:\n1. **Slack**: Slack uses GitHub for development and collaboration on their product.\n2. **Stripe**: Stripe leverages GitHub for their open-source projects and collaboration.\n3. **GitLab**: GitLab, although a competitor, hosts some of its open-source projects on GitHub.\n4. **Gatsby**: Gatsby, a popular static site generator, uses GitHub for development.\n5. **Docker**: Docker uses GitHub to host its open-source projects.\n6. **Elastic**: Elastic, the company behind Elasticsearch, hosts its open-source projects on GitHub.\n7. **HashiCorp**: HashiCorp uses GitHub for its open-source infrastructure tools.\n8. **Zapier**: Zapier uses GitHub for managing its codebase and collaboration.\n\n### Open Source Projects and Foundations:\n1. **Mozilla**: Mozilla hosts many of its open-source projects on GitHub.\n2. **Apache Software Foundation**: Some Apache projects are hosted on GitHub.\n3. **Linux Foundation**: Various projects under the Linux Foundation are hosted on GitHub.\n4. **Kubernetes**: Kubernetes, an open-source container orchestration system, is hosted on GitHub.\n5. **React**: The React library, developed by Facebook, is hosted on GitHub.\n\n### Other Examples:\n- **OpenAI**: OpenAI hosts some of its projects on GitHub.\n- **TensorFlow**: TensorFlow, an open-source machine learning library developed by Google, is hosted on GitHub.\n- **Node.js**: Node.js, a JavaScript runtime built on Chrome's V8 JavaScript engine, is hosted on GitHub.\n\nThese are just a few examples, but the utilization of GitHub spans a diverse range of industries and purposes, making it a central hub for software development and collaboration.",
